Purpose:
The function of this program is to read a bmp file which includes a few words in the picture and then separate them into individual character. 

Note:
* You can generate the your own bmp file by using Photoshop or any other picture handling program. 
* This program can be re-compiled in linux or Mac os environment by using GCC compiler with the attached Makefile. 

-f input file (Test.bmp)
-w input file's width 
-h input file's height
-c Generated file start number
-p The prefix of generated files

For example:
./sepFont -f Test.bmp -w 128 -h 24 -c 0 -p Tes
